Chicken Chow Mein

chow mein sauce:
2 tsp cornflour/cornstarch
1 1@ tbsp shoyu
1 1/2 tbsp oyster sauce
1 1/2 tbsp chinese cooking wine (or sherry)
2 tsp sugar
1/2 tsp sesame oil
white pepper

Mix togther cornflour/starch and shoyu, then mix in remaining ingredients.

real chinese ap stir fry sauce
1/4 c light shoyu
1/4 c shoyu
1/2 c oyster sauce
1/4 c chinese wine (or sherry)
1/4 c cornstarch/cornflour
1 tbsp sugar
2 tbsp sesame oil
1-2 tsp ground white pepper

Combine ingrdients in a jar and shake to combine. Store in refrigerator and shake before using.

200g (6oz) chicken thigh fillets (or breast) cut into bite size pieces
1/2 tsp baking soda (for velveting)
1 1/2 tbsp peanut oil
200g (6oz) fresh chow mein noodles
3-4 c green cabbage (savoy/green) finely shredded
1 carrot, julienned
1 c bean sprouts
3 shallot/scallions, cut into 5cm/2" pieces
2 cloves garlic, peeled and smashed
1/4 c (4 tbsp) water
1/4 c + 1 tbsp chow mein sauce (or "real chinese ap stir fry sauce)

Velveting the chicken: Combine chicken and baking soda in a small bowl and toss to combine. Set aside for 10 min to marinate, then rinse chicken well and pat dry. Pour 1 tbsp of sauce (either) over the chicken and set aside to marinate for 10 min. Prepare the noodles per packet instructions. Heat oil in wok or large fry pan over high heat. Add garlic and stir fry for 30 s until the garlic is golden brown and aromatic. Remove garlic from wok. Add chickn and stir fry until the skin is white but the inside is raw ~45 s to 1 min. Add the cabbage, carrot, and white pieces of shallots/scallions. Stir fry for 1-1 1/2 min until the cabbage is just starting to wilt and the chicken is cooked through. Add the noodles, sauce, and water. Stir fry for 1 min, tossing to coat the noodles in the sauce. Add bean sprouts and remaining shallots/scallions. Stir through quickly then remove from heat.
